SIMPLE: watershoot
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Watershoot
<hw>Wa"ter*shoot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
sprig or shoot from the root or stock of a tree.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>That which serves to guard from
falling water; a drip or dripstone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A trough for discharging water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water shrew</ent>⟦br⟧
